trans-unit.source: Represents a cell in a table.
Only a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.TableRowStructure> can be the parent of a TableCellStructure.

trans-unit.source: Every <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.TableCellStructure> must have at least one child.

Typically, a child is a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.ParagraphStructure>, but it can be a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.ListStructure>, <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.FigureStructure>, or a (nested) <xref:System.Windows.Documents.DocumentStructures.TableStructure>.
